Looking for Caribbean food made easy? Well, you are in luck if you live in the UK. Jamaica company Grace Foods has launched a Caribbean meal kit in Tesco, a British multinational groceries and general merchandise retailer headquartered in Welwyn Garden City, England. It is the third-largest retailer in the world measured by gross revenues and the ninth largest in the world by revenues. The range of the Irie Eats meal kits includes a microwaveable rice & peas side. Prices ranges between £1.75-£3.50/250g-515g. Others are: All products, according to Grace, are suitable for vegans and anyone can follow a simple five-step process to get the kits ready to serve. Grace Foods cited 2021 Mintel data, which revealed that nearly half or 49% of Brits said they would like to try Caribbean cuisine at home. “This is a significant and exciting opportunity for us to introduce authentic, traditional and flavorful Caribbean meal solutions to a new consumer audience,” Grace Foods brand manager Giuseppe Vullo was quoted as saying. “We’re excited to continue building awareness of Caribbean food in the UK market, providing a delicious and easy-to-use range inspired by classic island favorites.” Irie Eats became available from August 11th exclusively in Tesco stores nationwide in the UK, with wider distribution from December.